We can varaible like: 
	var a = 10;		# here you can reassign the value to variable "a"
	const b = 10		# here you can not reassign the value, It if fixed value.
	let x = 10		# Block scope

Example:-
        {					{
	  let x = 10				  varx = 10
	}					}

	// x can be used here			// x can be used here


In js their are 2 type of datatype and variables are declared with var keywords

1.)Primitive.
2.)Non-Primitive.

In primitive their are 5 types
	number		# in js integer and float both are same.
	string
	boolean
	undefined
	null

In Non-primitive their is only 1 types
	object (popularly know as reference data type, because we are using new keyword)


Example:-
	<!doctype>
	<head>
	<script type="text/javascript">
		var my_numberx = 10;
		document.write("value of my_numberx: "+ my_numberx + "<br>");		# o/p 10

		var my_numbery = 10.30;
		document.write("value of my_numbery: "+ my_numbery + "<br>");		# o/p 10.3

		var my_string = "Indra";
		document.write("value of my_string: "+ my_string+"<br/>");		# o/p Indra

		var my_undefined;
		document.write("value of my_undefined: "+ my_undefined + "<br/>");	# o/p undefined

		var my_null = null;
		document.write("value of my_null is: "+ my_null + '<br/>');		# o/p null

		var my_boolean = true;
		document.write("value of my_boolean:" + my_boolean + "<br/>";		# o/p true
		document.write("value of my_boolean:" + (100>101));			# o/p false
	</script>
	</head>



Dynamic change the type of varaiable like python in Js also available
	Example:-
		<head>
		<script type="text/javascript">
			var test = 10;
			alert("The value of test is: "+ test+ "and the type is: "+typeof(test));
			test = "indra"
			alert("The value of a is: "+test + "and the type is: "+typeof(test));
		</script>
		</head>
	
		output:- 10 number
			 indra string
